  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> steak[s] </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to one side of a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>miso paste </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Scrunch the<strong> tin foil</strong> around the corn until tightly sealed and add to the other side of the baking tray[s] – this is your <strong>miso butter corn</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the corn is tender and the wedges are golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> mirin</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, the <strong>remaining miso paste</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Japanese-style BBQ sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then season both sides with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned steak[s]</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until they're browned</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add your <strong>Japanese-style BBQ sauce</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked steak[s]</strong> to a clean chopping board and leave them to rest for 2 min, reserving the sauce in the pan – this is your <strong>Japanese-style BBQ pork loin</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the wedges are golden and crisp, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add your <strong>shichimi togarashi</strong> to the wedges and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>togarashi wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/japanese-style-bbq-pork-loin-with-miso-butter-corn/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Japanese-style BBQ pork loin</strong> and pour over the <strong>reserved sauce</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>miso butter corn</strong> and <strong>togarashi wedges</strong> to the side and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
